-- London Metal Exchange Adds Glencore’s Caplan to Aluminum Panel
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2013-07-05T08:33:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-05/london-metal-exchange-adds-glencore-s-caplan-to-aluminum-panel.html
The London Metal Exchange appointed
Andrew Caplan, head of Glencore Xstrata Plc’s aluminum division,
to its aluminum committee, according to the bourse’s website.  Sam Hainsworth of  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  also was named to
the panel, which is scheduled to hold its next meeting Oct. 9.
The LME committees comprise producers, consumers and traders of
the industrial metals bought and sold on the exchange. The
aluminum committee has 12 members including United Co. Rusal,
Alcoa Inc. and Trafigura Beheer BV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
